ZH: 他努力压下了自己的愤怒。
EN: He tried to suppress his anger.

ZH: 她努力压下了眼泪。
EN: She tried to hold back her tears.

ZH: 在这种危险的情况下，他必须压下恐惧。
EN: In such a dangerous situation, he must suppress his fear.

ZH: 他硬是压下了心头的怒火。
EN: He forcibly suppressed his anger.

ZH: 想要成功，必须要学会压下自己的贪婪。
EN: To succeed, one must learn to suppress their greed.

ZH: 我们不能随意压下人们的呼声。
EN: We cannot silence people's voices at will.

ZH: 她试图压下来自内心的不安。
EN: She tried to suppress the uneasiness from within.

ZH: 在职场上，压下情绪是非常重要的。
EN: In the workplace, suppressing emotions is very important.

ZH: 他越是想压下，心里的压力越是大。
EN: The more he tried to suppress it, the greater the pressure in his heart.

ZH: 随着越来越多的疑问，她再也无法压下内心的恐惧。
EN: With more and more doubts, she could no longer suppress her fear.

ZH: 对不公正的事情，不能永远压下去。
EN: Injustice cannot be suppressed forever.

ZH: 当情绪积压过多，很容易就会控制不住，需及时压下。
EN: When emotions are too pent up, it's easy to lose control, so they must be suppressed in time.

ZH: 你不应该压下自己真实的情感。
EN: You shouldn't suppress your true emotions.

ZH: 当生气的时候，最好尽量压下来。
EN: When angry, it's best to try to suppress it.

ZH: 压下不满，积极解决问题。
EN: Suppress dissatisfaction and actively solve the problem.

ZH: 地震的时候，人们总是用手压下桌子来寻找庇护。
EN: During an earthquake, people always press down on the table to seek shelter.

ZH: 每次想哭时都强迫自己压下眼泪。
EN: Every time she wants to cry, she forces back her tears.

ZH: 压下愤怒，理智决策。
EN: Suppress anger and make rational decisions.

ZH: 当面对困难时，我们要保持冷静，压下恐惧。
EN: When facing difficulties, we must stay calm and suppress fear.

ZH: 在压下不满的同时，也要及时沟通解决问题。
EN: While suppressing dissatisfaction, it is also important to communicate and resolve issues promptly.
